comments: Richardson (BOS) makes contact to Wagner's (ORL) body on the drive that affects his SQBR.
Brown (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Carter Jr. (ORL) and makes marginal contact to his body.
Carter Jr. (ORL) makes contact with Brown's (BOS) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) makes contact with Ross' (ORL) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Richardson (BOS) and Carter Jr. (ORL) mutually engage during the rebound and the contact is marginal.
Ross (ORL) makes marginal contact with two hands to Williams' (BOS) body that doesn't affect his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) gathers the ball and legally takes two steps to the basket.
Harris (ORL) places two hands on Smart's (BOS) body during the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Harris (ORL) makes marginal contact with Smart's (BOS) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact with Wagner's (ORL) arm during the steal.
Wagner (ORL) does not release the throw-in within five seconds.
Frazier (ORL) makes marginal contact to Brown's (BOS) arm during the drive.
Schroder (BOS) makes marginal contact with Frazier's (ORL) body that does not affect his shot near the rim.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock is set to 00:00.6.  The timeout by the Magic was recognized after the pass by Carter Jr. (ORL) to Frazier (ORL), who possessed the ball with 0.6 seconds remaining on the game clock and the Magic cannot advance the ball following the timeout.
Richardson (BOS) lifts his foot during his spin move.
Williams (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Wagner (ORL) and the contact is marginal.

Wagner (ORL) makes marginal head contact with Schroder (BOS) with his forearm during the pick. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Ross (ORL) places a hand/arm to Brown's (BOS) front during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Williams (BOS) legally contests the jump shot by Ross (ORL) and avoids initiating any contact that affects the jump shot attempt.
Frazier (ORL) makes contact to Richardson's (BOS) body that affects his FOM.
Richardson (BOS) dislodges Carter Jr. (ORL) from his position during the rebound.
Harris (ORL) briefly makes contact with two hands to Schroder's (BOS) body during his drive, but the contact is marginal.
Harris (ORL) reaches in and makes no contact to Schroder's (BOS) arm at the end of his drive.
Brown (BOS) makes contact to Wagner's (ORL) arm that affects his ability to control the rebound.
Frazier (ORL) commits a take foul on Schroder (BOS).
Richardson (BOS) moves into Frazier (ORL) and initiates contact that causes him to lose his balance.
Harris (ORL) commits a take foul on Schroder (BOS).
